  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HAIR SALON MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>The Salon Manager will oversee the daily operations of the salon to ensure smooth workflow, excellent customer service, and achievement of business goals. The role requires a combination of leadership, client relationship management, and operational expertise to maintain high standards of salon performance.</p><p>Key Responsibilities</p><p>Supervise daily salon operations, including staff scheduling, client appointments, and overall salon cleanliness.</p><p>Lead, motivate, and train hairstylists and support staff to deliver quality services.</p><p>Manage inventory, including hair products, equipment, and supplies.</p><p>Ensure compliance with workplace safety and hygiene regulations.</p><p>Handle customer inquiries, feedback, and complaints in a professional manner.</p><p>Oversee cash handling, billing, and daily sales reconciliation.</p><p>Plan and execute promotional activities to attract and retain clients.</p><p>Monitor performance metrics and prepare regular business reports for the owner.</p><p>Maintain strong client relationships and promote repeat business.</p><p>Support recruitment and performance evaluations of salon employees.</p><p>Requirements</p><p>Diploma or Certificate in Hairdressing, Salon Management, or Business Administration (preferred).</p><p>Minimum 3–5 years of experience in the hair or beauty industry, with at least 1–2 years in a supervisory or managerial role.</p><p>Strong communication and leadership skills.</p><p>Excellent knowledge of salon operations and hair/beauty products.</p><p>Customer-oriented with a pleasant personality.</p><p>Ability to work weekends and public holidays when required.</p>",
